      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">3 Elizabeth Street ¶ Hobart Town ¶ Tasmania ¶ Oct 2. 1877 ¶ My dear Baron....</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">77.10.02</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From W. W. Spicer</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M72, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by M: 'Answ 9/10'. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>
               <note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Cuscuta epithymum</seg> (MEL 2245850).</p>
               </note>3 Elizabeth Street</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Hobart Town</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Tasmania</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Oct 2. 1877</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Baron.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Will you kindly tell me what is the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Potamageton marinus L.</hi>
               </seg> of your Census? I have no specimens, &amp; our Library is so badly off for Botanical works, that I have no means of reference. Is it closely allied to <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">P. pectinatens L.</hi>
               </seg>? J. Hooker in his British Flora gives 2 Subspecies of P. pectinatus — pectinatus proper = "P. marinus Hud." &amp; filiformis Pers = "P. pectinatus Linn. Herb." Is either of these ours?</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A thousand thanks for naming a batch of plants for me some time ago. I ought to have thanked you before — but the fact is I had hoped to be able to tell you something about the habitat of <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Helichrysum Gravesii</hi>
               </seg>. But communication with the islands is so slow &amp; uncertain, that I have not yet had an answer.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I long to put back <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Brachycome</hi>
               </seg> into <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Bellis</hi>
               </seg>! Surely the slight differences between them are scarcely sufficient to warrant their separation. However much wiser heads than mine have acquiesced in it — yours among the rest.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You asked me some time ago to send you certain plants if I came across them, in Gunn's Herbarium.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>R. C. Gunn had presented his herbarium to the Royal Society of Tasmania. It was subsequently transferred to Sydney.</p>
               </note> You named Cuscuta. This is the only one I have found at present, &amp; enclose you a bit. It is marked</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">"Launceston</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">January, 1864".</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Should I find any others you may depend upon my sending you specimens.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I remain</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Yrs very truly</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>W. W. Spicer.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">P.S. Don't forget when you write, to do so in German!</p>
         </div>
      </body>
